==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obtest
<hw>Ob*test"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Obtested</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Obtesting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>obtestari</ets>;
<ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>) + <ets>testari</ets> to witness, fr.
<ets>testis</ets> a witness.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To call to witness;
to invoke as a witness.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To beseech; to supplicate; to beg for.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obtest</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Obtest
